From Edward Ted Fischer Subject Re Notes on Jays vs Indians Series In article A Edward Ouellette writes My point RBI might not be a perfect stat but nothing is And no stat or lack of can tell me there are no clutch hitters Maybe no stat CAN tell me, either, but some people are I just know it I was hoping somebody would mention clutch Clutch Baerga The two words simply do not go together With runners in scoring position, Baerga batted last year This doesn't quite suck , but most batters hit better in this situation Alomar He hit with runners in scoring position The difference Alomar had RBIs in such AB Baerga had RBIs in such AB Baerga got more chances, yet succeeded only more times Frankly, I don't believe in clutch But if I did, my vote would go to Alomar for MVP let alone best B in the AL Valentine